  <!-- FAQ JSON-LD Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to turn off caps lock on Chromebook?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To turn off caps lock on a Chromebook, simply press the <strong>Launcher (Search/Everything) key + Alt</strong> together, or tap the dedicated caps lock key if your Chromebook has one. On most Chromebooks the caps lock key is replaced by the Launcher key, so the Launcher + Alt shortcut is the standard way to toggle caps lock on and off. You can confirm it is disabled by watching the on-screen indicator or by using this caps lock test.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to turn on caps lock on a Chromebook?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To turn on caps lock on a Chromebook, press the <strong>Launcher (Search) key + Alt</strong> at the same time. A small notification usually appears confirming that caps lock is enabled. Pressing the same Launcher + Alt combination again turns it back off. You can also remap the Launcher key to act as a permanent caps lock key from Settings &rarr; Device &rarr; Keyboard.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to turn off caps lock?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>On a standard Windows or Mac keyboard, press the <strong>Caps Lock</strong> key once to turn it off. The Caps Lock key sits on the left side of the keyboard, directly above the Shift key and below the Tab key. When caps lock is off, the keyboard's caps lock LED turns off and letters type in lowercase. Use this caps lock test to confirm the current state instantly.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to disable caps lock?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To permanently disable the caps lock key, remap it through your operating system. On <strong>Windows</strong>, open Settings and use PowerToys' Keyboard Manager to remap Caps Lock to 'Undefined' or another key. On <strong>macOS</strong>, go to System Settings &rarr; Keyboard &rarr; Keyboard Shortcuts &rarr; Modifier Keys and set Caps Lock to 'No Action'. On <strong>Linux</strong>, tools like setxkbmap or GNOME Tweaks let you disable it. This stops caps lock from toggling at all.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to turn on auto caps lock?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Auto caps lock (auto-capitalization) is a mobile keyboard feature that automatically capitalizes the first letter of each sentence. On <strong>Android</strong>, open Settings &rarr; System &rarr; Languages &amp; input &rarr; your keyboard (e.g. Gboard) &rarr; Text correction, then enable 'Auto-capitalization'. On <strong>iPhone/iPad</strong>, go to Settings &rarr; General &rarr; Keyboard and turn on 'Auto-Capitalization'. Physical desktop keyboards do not have an auto caps lock mode.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Why is my caps lock reversed?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A reversed caps lock &mdash; where typing lowercase produces capitals and vice versa &mdash; usually happens when caps lock is enabled while you also hold Shift, or when a keyboard remapping or accessibility setting has inverted the behavior. Toggle the Caps Lock key once, release Shift, and re-test. If it stays reversed, check for third-party remapping software or a stuck Shift key. This caps lock test shows the true software state reported by your OS to help you diagnose the mismatch.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to caps lock in Excel?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Excel has no built-in caps lock toggle, but you can force uppercase text with the <strong>UPPER function</strong>. Type <code>=UPPER(A1)</code> in a cell to convert the text in cell A1 to all capitals. To type in caps directly, simply press the physical Caps Lock key on your keyboard, then type. For permanent uppercase entry across a column, apply the UPPER formula and paste the result back as values.</p>"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  </script>

