      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- LED-vs-Software mismatch guidance -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-2">
      <div class="card-base p-4 flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-xs text-primary uppercase tracking-wider flex items-center gap-1.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-brand-coral"></span>
          Physical LED vs Software State Mismatch
        </h3>
        <p class="text-[11px] text-slate leading-relaxed">
          Some external and wireless keyboards maintain a local Caps Lock LED state independent of the OS status. If your keyboard was toggled while unplugged, or during system boot, the physical keyboard LED and the system's software state can fall out of sync. This tester displays the <strong>true software state reported by the OS</strong>.
        </p>
